cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with measuring similarity between polygonal curves in the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes an algorithm to compute the Frechet distance between two polygonal curves. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with discrete versions of the Frechet distance. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the Frechet problem and its relation to the 3SUM problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions an algebraic decision tree for the Frechet problem, which is related to control theory.
